A new version of Avengers: Endgame will launch in South African cinemas starting Friday 12 July, offering moviegoers a look at new and deleted scenes. Reports that a new version of the highly-popular film would re-release with additional footage first surfaced a week ago, with Marvel Studios president Kevin Feige confirming the news. As of 19 June, Avengers: Endgame had grossed $2.742 billion globally and was closing in on Avatar which holds the box office record of $2.787 billion. This re-release of Avengers: Endgame may ensure that the movie tops this record to become the highest grossing film of all time. The updated showing will be available at a number of Ster Kinekor and Nu Metro cinemas across South Africa. Below is the full list of cinemas which will screen the new version of Avengers: Endgame: The new footage included in this re-release comprises the following scenes: Pre-feature Post-credits Spider-Man: Far From Home is set after the events of Avengers: Endgame in the Marvel cinematic universe, and will launch in cinemas on 3 July 2019. Nu Metro confirmed to MyBroadband that the re-release of Avengers: Endgame would only be screened in 2D. Below is the official Marvel Studios “Bring Back” poster for the Avengers: Endgame re-release. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-311813" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AVENGERS-ENDGAME-WLY3000.jpg" alt="AVENGERS ENDGAME WLY3000" width="640" height="935" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AVENGERS-ENDGAME-WLY3000.jpg 1694w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AVENGERS-ENDGAME-WLY3000-274x400.jpg 274w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AVENGERS-ENDGAME-WLY3000-768x1122.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AVENGERS-ENDGAME-WLY3000-294x430.jpg 294w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AVENGERS-ENDGAME-WLY3000-1200x1753.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-